	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your logic is flawed.  The haste percentage doesn't reduce the delay by that amount.  Rather, it increases the damage over time by that amount by adjusting the delay.  Not quite the same thing.<br><br>1 / (1/delay * (1 + Haste))<br><br>1/50 * 1.10 = 0.22<br>1/0.22 = 45.45 (which in this case rounds to 45)<br><br>However, if the haste was 100% (doing twice as much damage over time), the delay would be 25, *not* 0.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
